   <head>Dying Speech of an Old Philosopher</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="Sicilian Quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+-+-+-+-+">I strove with none, for none was worth my strife:</l>
     <l n="2" met="+--+-+-+-+">Nature I loved, and, next to Nature, Art:</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+++-+-+-+">I warm'd both hands before the fire of Life;</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+-+-+-+-+">It sinks; and I am ready to depart.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
